children.name: tar
children.synopsis: Package tar implements access to tar archives.

children.name: zip
children.synopsis: Package zip provides support for reading and writing ZIP archives.

name: bufio
synopsis: Package bufio implements buffered I/O. It wraps an io.Reader or io.Writer object, creating another object (Reader or Writer) that also implements the interface but provides buffering and some help for textual I/O.

name: builtin
synopsis: Package builtin provides documentation for Go's predeclared identifiers.

name: bytes
synopsis: Package bytes implements functions for the manipulation of byte slices.

children.name: bzip2
children.synopsis: Package bzip2 implements bzip2 decompression.

children.name: flate
children.synopsis: Package flate implements the DEFLATE compressed data format, described in RFC 1951.

children.name: gzip
children.synopsis: Package gzip implements reading and writing of gzip format compressed files, as specified in RFC 1952.

children.name: lzw
children.synopsis: Package lzw implements the Lempel-Ziv-Welch compressed data format, described in T. A. Welch, “A Technique for High-Performance Data Compression”, Computer, 17(6) (June 1984), pp 8-19.

children.name: zlib
children.synopsis: Package zlib implements reading and writing of zlib format compressed data, as specified in RFC 1950.

children.name: heap
children.synopsis: Package heap provides heap operations for any type that implements heap.Interface.

children.name: list
children.synopsis: Package list implements a doubly linked list.

children.name: ring
children.synopsis: Package ring implements operations on circular lists.

name: context
synopsis: Package context defines the Context type, which carries deadlines, cancellation signals, and other request-scoped values across API boundaries and between processes.

name: crypto
synopsis: Package crypto collects common cryptographic constants.

children.name: aes
children.synopsis: Package aes implements AES encryption (formerly Rijndael), as defined in U.S. Federal Information Processing Standards Publication 197.

children.name: cipher
children.synopsis: Package cipher implements standard block cipher modes that can be wrapped around low-level block cipher implementations.

children.name: des
children.synopsis: Package des implements the Data Encryption Standard (DES) and the Triple Data Encryption Algorithm (TDEA) as defined in U.S. Federal Information Processing Standards Publication 46-3.

children.name: dsa
children.synopsis: Package dsa implements the Digital Signature Algorithm, as defined in FIPS 186-3.

children.name: ecdsa
children.synopsis: Package ecdsa implements the Elliptic Curve Digital Signature Algorithm, as defined in FIPS 186-3.

children.name: ed25519
children.synopsis: Package ed25519 implements the Ed25519 signature algorithm.

children.name: elliptic
children.synopsis: Package elliptic implements several standard elliptic curves over prime fields.

children.name: hmac
children.synopsis: Package hmac implements the Keyed-Hash Message Authentication Code (HMAC) as defined in U.S. Federal Information Processing Standards Publication 198.

children.name: md5
children.synopsis: Package md5 implements the MD5 hash algorithm as defined in RFC 1321.

children.name: rand
children.synopsis: Package rand implements a cryptographically secure random number generator.

children.name: rc4
children.synopsis: Package rc4 implements RC4 encryption, as defined in Bruce Schneier's Applied Cryptography.

children.name: rsa
children.synopsis: Package rsa implements RSA encryption as specified in PKCS#1.

children.name: sha1
children.synopsis: Package sha1 implements the SHA-1 hash algorithm as defined in RFC 3174.

children.name: sha256
children.synopsis: Package sha256 implements the SHA224 and SHA256 hash algorithms as defined in FIPS 180-4.

children.name: sha512
children.synopsis: Package sha512 implements the SHA-384, SHA-512, SHA-512/224, and SHA-512/256 hash algorithms as defined in FIPS 180-4.

children.name: subtle
children.synopsis: Package subtle implements functions that are often useful in cryptographic code but require careful thought to use correctly.

children.name: tls
children.synopsis: Package tls partially implements TLS 1.2, as specified in RFC 5246, and TLS 1.3, as specified in RFC 8446.

children.name: x509
children.synopsis: Package x509 parses X.509-encoded keys and certificates.

children.name: pkix
children.synopsis: Package pkix contains shared, low level structures used for ASN.1 parsing and serialization of X.509 certificates, CRL and OCSP.

children.name: sql
children.synopsis: Package sql provides a generic interface around SQL (or SQL-like) databases.

children.name: driver
children.synopsis: Package driver defines interfaces to be implemented by database drivers as used by package sql.

children.name: dwarf
children.synopsis: Package dwarf provides access to DWARF debugging information loaded from executable files, as defined in the DWARF 2.0 Standard at http://dwarfstd.org/doc/dwarf-2.0.0.pdf

children.name: elf
children.synopsis: Package elf implements access to ELF object files.

children.name: gosym
children.synopsis: Package gosym implements access to the Go symbol and line number tables embedded in Go binaries generated by the gc compilers.

children.name: macho
children.synopsis: Package macho implements access to Mach-O object files.

children.name: pe
children.synopsis: Package pe implements access to PE (Microsoft Windows Portable Executable) files.

children.name: plan9obj
children.synopsis: Package plan9obj implements access to Plan 9 a.out object files.

name: encoding
synopsis: Package encoding defines interfaces shared by other packages that convert data to and from byte-level and textual representations.

children.name: ascii85
children.synopsis: Package ascii85 implements the ascii85 data encoding as used in the btoa tool and Adobe's PostScript and PDF document formats.

children.name: asn1
children.synopsis: Package asn1 implements parsing of DER-encoded ASN.1 data structures, as defined in ITU-T Rec X.690.

children.name: base32
children.synopsis: Package base32 implements base32 encoding as specified by RFC 4648.

children.name: base64
children.synopsis: Package base64 implements base64 encoding as specified by RFC 4648.

children.name: binary
children.synopsis: Package binary implements simple translation between numbers and byte sequences and encoding and decoding of varints.

children.name: csv
children.synopsis: Package csv reads and writes comma-separated values (CSV) files.

children.name: gob
children.synopsis: Package gob manages streams of gobs - binary values exchanged between an Encoder (transmitter) and a Decoder (receiver).

children.name: hex
children.synopsis: Package hex implements hexadecimal encoding and decoding.

children.name: json
children.synopsis: Package json implements encoding and decoding of JSON as defined in RFC 7159.

children.name: pem
children.synopsis: Package pem implements the PEM data encoding, which originated in Privacy Enhanced Mail.

children.name: xml
children.synopsis: Package xml implements a simple XML 1.0 parser that understands XML name spaces.

name: errors
synopsis: Package errors implements functions to manipulate errors.

name: expvar
synopsis: Package expvar provides a standardized interface to public variables, such as operation counters in servers.

name: flag
synopsis: Package flag implements command-line flag parsing.

name: fmt
synopsis: Package fmt implements formatted I/O with functions analogous to C's printf and scanf.

children.name: ast
children.synopsis: Package ast declares the types used to represent syntax trees for Go packages.

children.name: build
children.synopsis: Package build gathers information about Go packages.

children.name: constant
children.synopsis: Package constant implements Values representing untyped Go constants and their corresponding operations.

children.name: doc
children.synopsis: Package doc extracts source code documentation from a Go AST.

children.name: format
children.synopsis: Package format implements standard formatting of Go source.

children.name: importer
children.synopsis: Package importer provides access to export data importers.

children.name: parser
children.synopsis: Package parser implements a parser for Go source files.

children.name: printer
children.synopsis: Package printer implements printing of AST nodes.

children.name: scanner
children.synopsis: Package scanner implements a scanner for Go source text.

children.name: token
children.synopsis: Package token defines constants representing the lexical tokens of the Go programming language and basic operations on tokens (printing, predicates).

children.name: types
children.synopsis: Package types declares the data types and implements the algorithms for type-checking of Go packages.

name: hash
synopsis: Package hash provides interfaces for hash functions.

children.name: adler32
children.synopsis: Package adler32 implements the Adler-32 checksum.

children.name: crc32
children.synopsis: Package crc32 implements the 32-bit cyclic redundancy check, or CRC-32, checksum.

children.name: crc64
children.synopsis: Package crc64 implements the 64-bit cyclic redundancy check, or CRC-64, checksum.

children.name: fnv
children.synopsis: Package fnv implements FNV-1 and FNV-1a, non-cryptographic hash functions created by Glenn Fowler, Landon Curt Noll, and Phong Vo.

name: html
synopsis: Package html provides functions for escaping and unescaping HTML text.

children.name: template
children.synopsis: Package template (html/template) implements data-driven templates for generating HTML output safe against code injection.

name: image
synopsis: Package image implements a basic 2-D image library.

children.name: color
children.synopsis: Package color implements a basic color library.

children.name: palette
children.synopsis: Package palette provides standard color palettes.

children.name: draw
children.synopsis: Package draw provides image composition functions.

children.name: gif
children.synopsis: Package gif implements a GIF image decoder and encoder.

children.name: jpeg
children.synopsis: Package jpeg implements a JPEG image decoder and encoder.

children.name: png
children.synopsis: Package png implements a PNG image decoder and encoder.

children.name: suffixarray
children.synopsis: Package suffixarray implements substring search in logarithmic time using an in-memory suffix array.

name: io
synopsis: Package io provides basic interfaces to I/O primitives.

children.name: ioutil
children.synopsis: Package ioutil implements some I/O utility functions.

name: log
synopsis: Package log implements a simple logging package.

children.name: syslog
children.synopsis: Package syslog provides a simple interface to the system log service.

name: math
synopsis: Package math provides basic constants and mathematical functions.

children.name: big
children.synopsis: Package big implements arbitrary-precision arithmetic (big numbers).

children.name: bits
children.synopsis: Package bits implements bit counting and manipulation functions for the predeclared unsigned integer types.

children.name: cmplx
children.synopsis: Package cmplx provides basic constants and mathematical functions for complex numbers.

children.name: rand
children.synopsis: Package rand implements pseudo-random number generators.

name: mime
synopsis: Package mime implements parts of the MIME spec.

children.name: multipart
children.synopsis: Package multipart implements MIME multipart parsing, as defined in RFC 2046.

children.name: quotedprintable
children.synopsis: Package quotedprintable implements quoted-printable encoding as specified by RFC 2045.

name: net
synopsis: Package net provides a portable interface for network I/O, including TCP/IP, UDP, domain name resolution, and Unix domain sockets.

children.name: http
children.synopsis: Package http provides HTTP client and server implementations.

children.name: cgi
children.synopsis: Package cgi implements CGI (Common Gateway Interface) as specified in RFC 3875.

children.name: cookiejar
children.synopsis: Package cookiejar implements an in-memory RFC 6265-compliant http.CookieJar.

children.name: fcgi
children.synopsis: Package fcgi implements the FastCGI protocol.

children.name: httptest
children.synopsis: Package httptest provides utilities for HTTP testing.

children.name: httptrace
children.synopsis: Package httptrace provides mechanisms to trace the events within HTTP client requests.

children.name: httputil
children.synopsis: Package httputil provides HTTP utility functions, complementing the more common ones in the net/http package.

children.name: pprof
children.synopsis: Package pprof serves via its HTTP server runtime profiling data in the format expected by the pprof visualization tool.

children.name: mail
children.synopsis: Package mail implements parsing of mail messages.

children.name: rpc
children.synopsis: Package rpc provides access to the exported methods of an object across a network or other I/O connection.

children.name: jsonrpc
children.synopsis: Package jsonrpc implements a JSON-RPC 1.0 ClientCodec and ServerCodec for the rpc package.

children.name: smtp
children.synopsis: Package smtp implements the Simple Mail Transfer Protocol as defined in RFC 5321.

children.name: textproto
children.synopsis: Package textproto implements generic support for text-based request/response protocols in the style of HTTP, NNTP, and SMTP.

children.name: url
children.synopsis: Package url parses URLs and implements query escaping.

name: os
synopsis: Package os provides a platform-independent interface to operating system functionality.

children.name: exec
children.synopsis: Package exec runs external commands.

children.name: signal
children.synopsis: Package signal implements access to incoming signals.

children.name: user
children.synopsis: Package user allows user account lookups by name or id.

name: path
synopsis: Package path implements utility routines for manipulating slash-separated paths.

children.name: filepath
children.synopsis: Package filepath implements utility routines for manipulating filename paths in a way compatible with the target operating system-defined file paths.

name: plugin
synopsis: Package plugin implements loading and symbol resolution of Go plugins.

name: reflect
synopsis: Package reflect implements run-time reflection, allowing a program to manipulate objects with arbitrary types.

name: regexp
synopsis: Package regexp implements regular expression search.

children.name: syntax
children.synopsis: Package syntax parses regular expressions into parse trees and compiles parse trees into programs.

name: runtime
synopsis: Package runtime contains operations that interact with Go's runtime system, such as functions to control goroutines.

children.name: cgo
children.synopsis: Package cgo contains runtime support for code generated by the cgo tool.

children.name: debug
children.synopsis: Package debug contains facilities for programs to debug themselves while they are running.

children.name: pprof
children.synopsis: Package pprof writes runtime profiling data in the format expected by the pprof visualization tool.

children.name: race
children.synopsis: Package race implements data race detection logic.

children.name: trace
children.synopsis: Package trace contains facilities for programs to generate traces for the Go execution tracer.

name: sort
synopsis: Package sort provides primitives for sorting slices and user-defined collections.

name: strconv
synopsis: Package strconv implements conversions to and from string representations of basic data types.

name: strings
synopsis: Package strings implements simple functions to manipulate UTF-8 encoded strings.

name: sync
synopsis: Package sync provides basic synchronization primitives such as mutual exclusion locks.

children.name: atomic
children.synopsis: Package atomic provides low-level atomic memory primitives useful for implementing synchronization algorithms.

name: syscall
synopsis: Package syscall contains an interface to the low-level operating system primitives.

children.name: js
children.synopsis: Package js gives access to the WebAssembly host environment when using the js/wasm architecture.

name: testing
synopsis: Package testing provides support for automated testing of Go packages.

children.name: iotest
children.synopsis: Package iotest implements Readers and Writers useful mainly for testing.

children.name: quick
children.synopsis: Package quick implements utility functions to help with black box testing.

children.name: scanner
children.synopsis: Package scanner provides a scanner and tokenizer for UTF-8-encoded text.

children.name: tabwriter
children.synopsis: Package tabwriter implements a write filter (tabwriter.Writer) that translates tabbed columns in input into properly aligned text.

children.name: template
children.synopsis: Package template implements data-driven templates for generating textual output.

children.name: parse
children.synopsis: Package parse builds parse trees for templates as defined by text/template and html/template.

name: time
synopsis: Package time provides functionality for measuring and displaying time.

name: unicode
synopsis: Package unicode provides data and functions to test some properties of Unicode code points.

children.name: utf16
children.synopsis: Package utf16 implements encoding and decoding of UTF-16 sequences.

children.name: utf8
children.synopsis: Package utf8 implements functions and constants to support text encoded in UTF-8.

name: unsafe
synopsis: Package unsafe contains operations that step around the type safety of Go programs.
